OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772110991
OL,3,CFormer Plymouth lawyer sentenced to 13
OL,4,Cyears for sexual offences
OL,6,FShe added: "They relied upon you as
OL,7,Ftheir legal adviser to help them when
OL,8,Fthey were in difficult circumstances.
OL,10,F"In some cases they were still under
OL,11,Finfluence of drugs or alcohol when you
OL,12,Fsexually abused them.
OL,14,F"All many wanted (was) for them to
OL,15,Fsecure their release as soon as
OL,16,Fpossible."
OL,26,@nD@LOUrD@AOUvD@AOUxD@JO]
