OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772110991
OL,3,CFormer Plymouth lawyer sentenced to 13
OL,4,Cyears for sexual offences
OL,6,FThe sentencing hearing, which began on
OL,7,FTuesday, had heard the impact on his
OL,8,Fvictims, with one man who was sexually
OL,9,Fassaulted by Harris telling the court
OL,10,Fthe abuse will "forever haunt" him.
OL,12,FOne victim spoke directly to Harris as
OL,13,Fhe recounted the impact of the abuse
OL,14,Fon his life, at a time when he had
OL,15,Ftrusted the solicitor.
OL,17,F"I will never understand or be able to
OL,18,Faccept your behaviour," he told Harris.
OL,20,F"Your actions will forever haunt me
OL,21,Fand will remain with me to the grave.
OL,26,@rD@POUrD@^O]yD@AOUzD@WO]|D@AOU
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G5/11
OL,2,W,.!+.-' "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BSW Eng NewsCThis Day FReg TV
FL,436,430,120,260,000,100
PN,43506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772110991
OL,3,CFormer Plymouth lawyer sentenced to 13
OL,4,Cyears for sexual offences
OL,6,F"I was young, I was scared and
OL,7,Fvulnerable. I was locked in a cell
OL,8,Fwith no escape."
OL,10,FHe added: "Your reputation lies in
OL,11,Ftatters and any good work you did is
OL,12,Fnow tarnished."
OL,14,FA second victim told the court how the
OL,15,Factions of Harris were a contributing
OL,16,Ffactor to his heroin addiction.
OL,18,F"I was happy when I heard the verdict
OL,19,Fthat I had been believed after all
OL,20,Fthis time," he said.
OL,26,@nD@AOUpD@PO]rD@KOUtD@OO]zD@AOU|D@KO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G6/11
