OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772110991
OL,3,CFormer Plymouth lawyer sentenced to 13
OL,4,Cyears for sexual offences
OL,6,FA third victim, who read his victim
OL,7,Fpersonal statement to the court,
OL,8,Fdescribed the lasting impact of
OL,9,FHarris's abuse.
OL,11,FHe told Harris: "There is no peace for
OL,12,Fme. There never will be.
OL,14,F"You will always be in my head. You
OL,15,Fwill always be in my nightmares."
OL,17,FProsecuting, Anne Whyte KC read
OL,18,Fstatements on behalf of other victims
OL,19,Fin the case.
OL,26,@sD@QOUvD@AOUwD@aO]
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G7/11
