OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F435A1772110991
OL,3,CFormer Plymouth lawyer sentenced to 13
OL,4,Cyears for sexual offences
OL,6,FDescribing his career, she told the
OL,7,Fcourt that the father-of-two had a
OL,8,F"very loyal following".
OL,10,F"He helped out hundreds if not
OL,11,Fthousands of clients over the years,"
OL,12,Fshe said.
OL,14,F"He had many clients who returned to
OL,15,Fhim because of the service provided.
OL,17,F"His fall from grace is a mighty one.
OL,18,FHe did enjoy extremely good standing
OL,19,Fin his local community.
OL,26,@pD@AOUpD@VO]rD@AOUsD@eO]vD@AOUyD@AOU
